17/05/2005
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- Serbia-Montenegro should proceed with dialogue for development of the federal union, Spanish Foreign Minister Miguel Angel Moratinos said on Monday (16 May), after a meeting with Montenegrin Prime Minister Milo Djukanovic. 
According to the Spanish diplomat, who is on an official two-day visit to Serbia-Montenegro, the republics should continue working together to benefit their citizens. 
Moratinos will meet with Foreign Minister Vuk Draskovic, Serbian President Boris Tadic and Prime Minister Vojislav Kostunica, as well as visit Pristina, on Tuesday. 
Moratinos will then travel to Bosnia and Herzegovina and Croatia. 
(Danas - 17/05/05; Beta - 16/05/05)
